        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 2:21PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lincoln, or 18 miles northeast of Ruidoso, and is stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ruidoso, Lincoln, Lincoln State Monument and Fort Stanton.

This includes Highway 380 between Mile Markers 89 and 102.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
